Merge pull request #2 from mozilla/initial-import-and-refactor

Split out fxa-basket-proxy into a standalone project; r=shane-tomlinson

Split out fxa-basket-proxy into a standalone project.

This commit imports the fxa-basket-proxy code from [1] as a standalone
project, splitting it up into smaller chunks and adding some basic
repo infrastructure and tests.  The logic of the code itself is unchanged
apart from some config-loading and logging tweaks.

[1] https://github.com/mozilla/fxa-content-server/blob/13a59b2457d373190f1853c513604a5b72bb5106/server/bin/basket-proxy-server.js

updates basket-proxy to accept both those things, while keeping
backwards compatibility with previous behaviour.

This provides a simple config option to disable the processing of
particular SQS event types.  We'll use it to slowly phase out our
own handling of these events in favour of native handling by basket.

chore(style): ES6-ify ./lib/events/index.js

In general we're converting existing code to ES6 as we make changes
to it, and I want to make some changes to ./lib/events/index.js.
But putting ES6 in this repo means updating our linting and coverage
tools to deal with that, so I'm doing it as a separate commit.
